<br>
You are one of the oldest friends I have had in the game, and one of the most respected and trusted players I have come across.  You taught me a lot in this silly game, and we talked about other things, in the real world and such.  Who am I going to share my fishing stories with?  Where is the warrior I had to lead through his first trip in Hate by the hand when the DKC was up for the challenge of raiding the plane?  I hope all is well with you, and with life.  You will certainly be missed my friend.  It brings a tear to my eye when I got home from my weekend and read this.  How could a game create such friends, whom we never met, but in turn we are going to miss the hell out of?  I could tell by the title what was going to happen, but I pressed on and read it from the start.  Over and over, in disbelief.  But we all have our paths that we must follow, and yours steers away from this game and down other avenues.<br>
<br>
I'm glad I got to make your aquaintance in the DKC, and later, friend for over the past year and a half.<br>
<br>
You will always be my brother and mentor, and I will miss you dearly.<br>
<br>
Good luck my friend, and please keep in touch, things will not be the same without you.  Drop me a line sometime...  lachlann@bonq.net<br>
<br>
/salute<br>
